neofetch is &ldquo;a command-line system information tool written in bash 3.2+&rdquo;
Some resources.  the github page here. the arch manual page here.  Dependencies for neofetch.  some art works in ~/.config/neofetch/ascii.  Install neofetch manually.  install the dependencies. install the neofetch command. copy config.conf, .neofetchrc and the files in ascii inside your ~/.config/neofetch directory.  Gallery. Available soon.
